  "worthless_belief": [],
  "intermediate_belief": "If I challenge authority or express disagreement, I will be rejected or dismissed, and it will confirm that my ideas are not valued. It's safer to avoid confrontation because standing up for myself will only lead to more conflict or prove that I'm inadequate.",
  "intermediate_belief_depression": "If my ideas are rejected and I don't stand up for them, it means I am not capable or respected, and nothing I do will make a difference.",
  "coping_strategies": "The client avoids direct confrontation with authority figures, withdrawing from discussions and not voicing opinions when their ideas are rejected. They may seek reassurance from colleagues to validate their methods, using avoidance and external validation to manage distress.",
  "situation": "Proposed a new teaching method that was rejected by school leadership. Does not confront leadership directly about the decision.",
  "auto_thought": "They don't value my ideas. If I speak up, it will just make things worse for me.",
