  "behavior": "Does not confront leadership about the rejection. Withdraws from further discussion and avoids bringing up the topic. May talk to colleagues for reassurance instead.",
  "rationale": "\"The rejection of the proposed teaching method likely evokes feelings of disappointment and frustration... The ongoing conflicts with authority figures may contribute to feelings of irritation or annoyance... The patient's decision not to confront leadership directly might stem from a belief that confrontation could lead to further rejection or conflict, reinforcing a pattern of avoidance... The patient appears to avoid direct confrontation with authority figures, possibly as a coping mechanism to prevent further conflict or rejection... The patient might also seek reassurance from colleagues or engage in discussions with peers to validate their teaching methods and alleviate feelings of inadequacy.\""
